## CRITICAL RULES
1. curated_data/ is READ-ONLY. Never modify or delete.
2. Colon_raw/ root 4 parquet files are EXCLUDED:
   - drug_features_catalog.parquet
   - drug_target_mapping.parquet
   - gdsc_ic50.parquet
   - lincs_drug_signature_normalized.parquet
3. Use ONLY these Colon_raw/ subdirectories:
   gdsc, depmap, lincs(GSE70138 only), drugbank, chembl, admet, cBioPortal, geo(GSE39582 only)
4. DO NOT USE: gtex, msigdb, opentargets, string (baseline first)
5. Copied scripts: modify ONLY BASE_DIR, paths, log messages. DO NOT change logic.
6. Before modifying copied scripts, show DIFF and get approval.
7. If error occurs, STOP and report. Do NOT solve arbitrarily.
8. If uncertain, say "I don't know" and ask user.
9. Do NOT use s3://say2-4team/20260409_eseo/ (not owned).

## LINCS Cell Line Policy (FIXED)
Include 13: CL34, HCT116, HT115, HT29, LOVO, MDST8, NCIH508, RKO, SNU1040, SNUC5, SW480, SW620, SW948
Exclude: HELA, HELA.311 (cervical), HT29.311 (Cas9), NCIH716 (no data)

## Subtype Tagging
- For evaluation stratification: COAD/READ, MSI
- Metadata only (no stratification): RAS, BRAF
- Skipped this round: HER2, CMS, sidedness

## When Writing Code
- Use pathlib over os.path
- Use f-strings
- Add docstrings with input/output shapes
- Log all file I/O with timestamps to logs/
- Never hardcode credentials
- Reference Lung/BRCA scripts by path comments when adapting

## Coding Environment
- Python 3.10, conda env: drug4
- pandas, pyarrow for parquet
- cmapPy for LINCS gctx parsing

## Before Each Action
- Show what files will be created/modified
- Get approval before destructive operations
- Run in order, confirm each step before next
